# wiki+ prototype — Caddy reverse proxy + automatic TLS (issue A.2 / #42).
#
# Caddy terminates TLS directly (Let's Encrypt, HTTP-01 by default) and reverse-proxies to
# the app container over the compose network. Cloudflare EDGE CACHE is deferred to the
# production-MVP (issue #35) — for the prototype Caddy is the public-facing TLS endpoint.
#
# !! DNS / Cloudflare CHECK (do NOT assume) — wikiplus.wikiedu.org is a subdomain of the
#    wikiedu.org zone, which may already be managed in Cloudflare. If the A/AAAA record for
#    wikiplus.wikiedu.org is created PROXIED (orange cloud) in Cloudflare, two things bite:
#      1. Caddy's HTTP-01 / TLS-ALPN challenge can fail or loop unless Cloudflare's SSL/TLS
#         mode for the zone is "Full" (or "Full (strict)" once Caddy holds a real cert) —
#         "Flexible" causes a redirect loop, and the edge intercepts :80/:443.
#      2. The simplest robust fix is to create the record as DNS-only (grey cloud) so Caddy
#         reaches Let's Encrypt directly; OR switch Caddy to a DNS-01 challenge using a
#         Cloudflare API token (needs the caddy-dns/cloudflare plugin — a custom Caddy build,
#         documented in the runbook as the fallback).
#    Confirm the zone's proxy status + SSL mode with the owner BEFORE first bring-up; the
#    config below assumes a directly-reachable origin (DNS-only record, or HTTP-01 works).

{
	# Operator contact for Let's Encrypt / ACME (expiry + policy notices).
	email sage@wikiedu.org
}

wikiplus.wikiedu.org {
	# Reverse-proxy to the app container (compose service name : container port).
	reverse_proxy app:3000

	encode zstd gzip

	# Access logs to stdout (captured by `docker compose logs caddy`), JSON for easy parsing.
	log {
		output stdout
		format json
	}
}
